============================== Description ===============================

prettyPhoto is a jQuery based lightbox clone. Not only does it support images,
it also add support for videos, flash, YouTube, iFrame. It's a full blown
media modal box.

Please refer to http://www.no-margin-for-errors.com/projects/prettyPhoto/
for all the details on how to use. 


============================== I18n ===============================

This version of prettyPhoto support multiple languages based
on the page <body> class and a set of override classes.

- first you need to define your current locale on the body tag : <body class="fr">
- locale CSS are located in /css/{locale}.css                                     
- localized images are stored in images/prettyPhoto/locales/{locale}/
- edit css/prettyPhoto.css and add any locale you need : @import url(fr.css);
- PSD for buttons are included, feel free to contribute new locale CSS and images.
- default locale is EN 